{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b1c455b3-ddb0-4903-aca1-ce7e5b09edb9","content":"**MSTest.Sdk 4.0+ dropped the VSTest compatibility layer by default.**\n\nStarting with MSTest.Sdk 4.0.0, the SDK uses **Microsoft.Testing.Platform** as the *only* test host. The VSTest bridge adapter (`Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.VSTestBridge`) is no longer included automatically, so `vstest.console` (and `dotnet test` in VSTest mode) can't discover or run your tests.\n\n### Your options:\n\n1. **Re-enable VSTest support** — add this to your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <EnableMicrosoftTestingExtensionsVSTestBridge>true</EnableMicrosoftTestingExtensionsVSTestBridge>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n2. **Switch your CI to the new runner** — replace `vstest.console` with:\n   ```bash\n   dotnet run --project TestProject.csproj -- --report-trx\n   ```\n   or use `dotnet test` which (in newer SDK versions) auto-detects Microsoft.Testing.Platform.\n\nOption 2 is the recommended long-term path since VSTest is being phased out.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"32be2652-ab44-4bdf-9efc-475fe9e7f7fe","outputTokens":280,"requestId":"481C:E3CA7:614BB72:69D3CFB:69FC01FC"},"id":"87139d88-1bc9-44cd-ab7d-3352a99aa8ad","timestamp":"2026-05-07T03:07:49.876Z","parentId":"b9226a7a-b545-4575-84bc-cac4f007746b"}
